title: ASU punter Matt Haack named Ray Guy Award Player of the Week
text:
ASU punter Matt Haack named Ray Guy Award Player of the Week FOX Sports 
Oct 5, 2015 at 1:11p ET + 
Haack was the nation's best punter in Week 5. Mark J. Rebilas-USA TODAY Sports FOX Sports   1:11p ET 
After an impressive showcase vs. UCLA, ASU punter Matt Haack was honored by the Augusta Sports Council Ray Guy Award Player of the Week. 
Haack had eight punts for 345 yards (43.1 yards per punt) during ASU's road victory over UCLA. Five of his punts landed within the 20-yard line (without a touchback) and one of his punts was 63 yards. One of his punts even landed at UCLA's own 1-yard line late in the game. true Unsung hero of ASU's win at UCLA: punter Matt Haack. Avg 43 yards on 8 punts, 5 of them inside the 20, 1 downed at the Bruin 1 late in game.
